# runctl Integration

## Quick Reference

**Location**: `../runctl` (sibling directory)

**Use for**: Instance lifecycle, spot management, SSM code sync, resource tracking

**Don't use for**: Task distribution (use SQS), custom infrastructure (use boto3/terraform)

## Critical Requirements

### IAM Permissions (MUST HAVE)

Instance profile **must** include SQS permissions or workers fail with `NonExistentQueue`:

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Allow",
    "Action": ["sqs:GetQueueUrl", "sqs:ReceiveMessage", "sqs:DeleteMessage", "sqs:SendMessage", "sqs:GetQueueAttributes"],
    "Resource": "arn:aws:sqs:REGION:ACCOUNT_ID:anno-eval-tasks"
  }]
}
```

**Add to role:**
```bash
ROLE_NAME=$(aws iam get-instance-profile --instance-profile-name anno-eval-spot-profile --query 'InstanceProfile.Roles[0].RoleName' --output text)
aws iam put-role-policy --role-name "$ROLE_NAME" --policy-name "anno-eval-sqs-policy" --policy-document file://sqs-policy.json
```

**Verify:**
```bash
aws ssm send-command --instance-ids <id> --document-name AWS-RunShellScript \
  --parameters 'commands=["aws sqs get-queue-url --queue-name anno-eval-tasks --region us-east-1"]'
```

### Configuration

**File**: `runctl.toml` (non-dot, not `.runctl.toml`)

```toml
[aws]
region = "us-east-1"
default_instance_type = "c7i.xlarge"
use_spot = true
s3_bucket = "arc-anno-data"
iam_instance_profile = "anno-eval-spot-profile"  # Must have SSM + SQS + S3
```

## Worker Setup Pattern

**Git clone fails in SSM context** - use one of:

1. **Git config** (public repos):
   ```bash
   export GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0
   git config --global credential.helper ""
   git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/arclabs561/anno.git /root/anno
   ```

2. **runctl code sync** (preferred):
   ```bash
   runctl aws sync-code <instance-id> --source . --target /root/anno
   ```

3. **S3 tarball** (private repos):
   ```bash
   aws s3 cp s3://bucket/src/anno-src.tar.gz /tmp/ && tar xzf /tmp/anno-src.tar.gz -C /root/anno
   ```

**Complete worker setup:**
```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e
export HOME=/root

# Dependencies
dnf install -y git gcc gcc-c++ openssl-devel pkg-config jq cmake || true

# Rust
if ! command -v cargo &>/dev/null; then
    curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y
    source $HOME/.cargo/env
fi

# Queue URL (with error handling)
QUEUE_URL=$(aws sqs get-queue-url --queue-name anno-eval-tasks --region us-east-1 --query QueueUrl --output text 2>&1) || QUEUE_URL=""
export ANNO_SPOT_QUEUE_URL=$QUEUE_URL

# Clone (handle git auth)
if [[ ! -d /root/anno ]]; then
    export GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0
    git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/arclabs561/anno.git /root/anno
fi

# Build
cd /root/anno
if [[ ! -f /opt/cache/target/release/anno ]]; then
    cargo build --release --bin anno --features "cli,eval-advanced,onnx" 2>&1 | tail -20
fi

# Start worker
nohup bash scripts/spot/worker.sh > /tmp/worker.log 2>&1 &
```

## Monitoring

**Queue status:**
```bash
QUEUE_URL=$(aws sqs get-queue-url --queue-name anno-eval-tasks --region us-east-1 --query QueueUrl --output text)
PENDING=$(aws sqs get-queue-attributes --queue-url "$QUEUE_URL" --attribute-names ApproximateNumberOfMessages --query 'Attributes.ApproximateNumberOfMessages' --output text)
IN_FLIGHT=$(aws sqs get-queue-attributes --queue-url "$QUEUE_URL" --attribute-names ApproximateNumberOfMessagesNotVisible --query 'Attributes.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesNotVisible' --output text)
```

**Worker status:**
```bash
aws ssm send-command --instance-ids <id> --document-name AWS-RunShellScript \
  --parameters 'commands=["pgrep -af worker.sh && echo Running || echo Not running; tail -50 /tmp/worker.log"]'
```

**Instance status:**
```bash
runctl aws status <instance-id>
```

## Common Issues

| Issue | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `NonExistentQueue` | Missing SQS permissions | Add inline policy to IAM role (see above) |
| `could not read Username` | Git auth prompt in SSM | Use `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` or runctl code sync |
| SSM not ready | Spot instance boot time | Wait up to 3 minutes with retries |
| Worker not starting | Binary not built | Check `/opt/cache/target/release/anno` exists |
| Queue access fails | IAM propagation delay | Wait 30-60 seconds after adding permissions |

## Key Learnings

- **`runctl.toml`** (non-dot) prioritized over `.runctl.toml`
- **SQS permissions** are critical - most common failure point
- **SSM wait time**: Up to 3 minutes for spot instances
- **IAM propagation**: 30-60 seconds after policy changes
- **Git clone**: Fails in SSM without proper config
- **Spot availability**: Use `c7i.xlarge` or larger (smaller types have poor availability)

## Commands

```bash
# Setup
just spot-runctl-setup

# Full eval
just spot-runctl-eval 1 c7i.xlarge

# Monitor
just spot-runctl-status

# Teardown
just spot-runctl-teardown
```

**Note**: All Python scripts use `uv run` to ensure dependencies (boto3, rich) are available. Scripts have PEP 723 inline metadata for automatic dependency management.
